"```sql\nSELECT \n    (COUNT(posts.Id) * 100.0 / (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM posts WHERE OwnerDisplayName = 'Community')) AS percentage\nFROM \n    posts\nJOIN \n    postLinks ON posts.Id = postLinks.PostId\nJOIN \n    tags ON postLinks.RelatedPostId = tags.ExcerptPostId\nWHERE \n    tags.TagName = 'r' AND posts.OwnerDisplayName = 'Community';\n``` \n\nThis SQL query calculates the percentage of posts that use the R language by counting the posts tagged with 'r' and dividing it by the total number of posts made by the user 'Community'."